  "texts": [
    "In addition to effect size differences between psychological profiles, we also found differences in the effectiveness of personalized persuasion across topics.",
    "For example, in Study 4, the matched messages were more effective for the experiential product (a Rome getaway) than they were for the material one (sneakers).",
    "These differences might be explained by a number of factors.",
    "For example, the experiential nature of the weekend getaway-with the opportunity to highlight different activities and aspects of the trip-might allow for more genuine and meaningful personalization than that for a pair of sneakers.",
    "Additionally, prior research has suggested that matching is more effective for expensive products 74, because people are more concerned about making the right choice in these instances."
  ],
